			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2021</a> paper:</span><br><i>Getting grammars into shape for block-based editors</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/MauricioVeranoMerino.html">Mauricio Verano Merino</a>, <a href="../profile/TomBeckmann.html">Tom Beckmann</a>, <a href="../profile/TijsvanderStorm.html">Tijs van der Storm</a>, <a href="../profile/RobertHirschfeld.html">Robert Hirschfeld</a>, <a href="../profile/JurgenVinju.html">Jurgen Vinju</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3486608.3486908">10.1145/3486608.3486908</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3b.html"><span class="tagM">T3B: Transformation Languages</span></a><ul><li> The paper’s central topic is specifying or applying transformations (rewriting/mapping/synchronization).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It includes substantial tool support or infrastructure relevant for engineering/using languages.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It performs mapping/conversion/synchronization between representations (horizontal transformations).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagL">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It uses compilation/generation/refinement to derive executable artifacts (vertical transformations).
</li></ul></li></ul>
